Exercise 05 — Valgrind: Use-After-Free
=========================================

The program frees a struct, then keeps using it.
This is a use-after-free bug — one of the most exploited
vulnerability classes in real-world software.

It may not crash. It may print plausible-looking values.
That is what makes it dangerous.

Your goal: use Valgrind to detect and understand the bug.

  Run with Valgrind:
    valgrind --leak-check=full ./target

  Answer these questions:
    - What does Valgrind call this type of error?
    - At which line does the invalid access occur?
    - Why might this bug be silent without Valgrind?

When you can answer all three AND have read the flag with GDB, submit it: horizon done HRZ{...}
